; Tests for history.cc: price inversion and conversion paths
; Covers: lines 372-378 (price inversion when price.commodity == source)
;         lines 396-397 (return nullopt when source == target)

; Price defined inversely: $ priced in EUR
; When looking up EUR -> $, the graph has an edge $ -> EUR
; so price inversion is needed (lines 372-378)
P 2024/01/01 $ 0.91 EUR

2024/01/15 Test
    Expenses  10 EUR
    Assets

; Converting EUR to $ requires inverting the $ -> EUR price
test bal -X '$'
                $-11  Assets
                 $11  Expenses
--------------------
                   0
end test
